<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1525,2015]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,255]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1872,1898]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body elongate-oval, yellowish to reddish brown, shining. Length of pronotum + elytra = 2.4–3.6 mm (males), 2.3–3.7 mm (females); pronotum broad, ratio length:width = 1:1.6; elytra of medium proportions, ratio length:width = 1:0.7. Antennal club (
<figureCitation box="[818,890,1950,1976]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–13" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1289,1313]" captionTargetBox="[237,1354,203,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-243@10.[233,1354,197,1264]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8–13. Triarthron lecontei. 8. Right antenna, dorsal view. 9. Mandibles, dorsal view. 10. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 11. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 12. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 13. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 11, 13), 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 9, 12), 0.75 mm (Fig. 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310890/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) moderately broad, ratio club width:length = 1:2.8; antennomeres 6 and 7 equal in width, width ratio of antennomeres 6:7:8:9 = 1:1:1.2:2.0. Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[160,235,1733,1759]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–13" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1289,1313]" captionTargetBox="[237,1354,203,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-243@10.[233,1354,197,1264]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8–13. Triarthron lecontei. 8. Right antenna, dorsal view. 9. Mandibles, dorsal view. 10. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 11. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 12. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 13. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 11, 13), 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 9, 12), 0.75 mm (Fig. 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310890/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) moderately elongate; right mandible with an elongate sub-apical tooth and an additional poorly defined tooth on apical one-half of inner margin; inner margin of left mandible with a thin, narrow plate on apical one-half and a tooth on basal one-half. Profemur and mesofemur of both sexes serrulate on posterior margins; female metafemur serrulate on posterior margin; male metafemur (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1155,1849,1875]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–13" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1289,1313]" captionTargetBox="[237,1354,203,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-243@10.[233,1354,197,1264]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8–13. Triarthron lecontei. 8. Right antenna, dorsal view. 9. Mandibles, dorsal view. 10. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 11. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 12. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 13. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 11, 13), 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 9, 12), 0.75 mm (Fig. 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310890/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig.10</figureCitation>
) with ventral region of posterior margin serrulate, dorsal margin with 3–6 small teeth, broad tooth-like lamina dorsally and ventrally at apex of posterior margin. All tibiae of male and female slender, of uniform diameter in apical three-fourths, not widened at apex, lacking distinct tarsal groove, outer margins spinose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1061,1133,1964,1990]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Male.</emphasis>
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1364,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–13" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1289,1313]" captionTargetBox="[237,1354,203,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-243@10.[233,1354,197,1264]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8–13. Triarthron lecontei. 8. Right antenna, dorsal view. 9. Mandibles, dorsal view. 10. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 11. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 12. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 13. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 11, 13), 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 9, 12), 0.75 mm (Fig. 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310890/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) with median lobe broad at base, evenly tapering to narrowly rounded apex. Parameres not reaching apex of median lobe, slender, with 3–4 apical setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[572,670,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Female.</emphasis>
Coxites (
<figureCitation box="[782,860,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–13" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1289,1313]" captionTargetBox="[237,1354,203,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-243@10.[233,1354,197,1264]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8–13. Triarthron lecontei. 8. Right antenna, dorsal view. 9. Mandibles, dorsal view. 10. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 11. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 12. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 13. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 11, 13), 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 9, 12), 0.75 mm (Fig. 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310890/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig.13</figureCitation>
) moderately elongate, cylindrical, with subapical setae; styli elongate, inserted at apices of coxites, with elongate apical setae. Sternite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1319,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–13" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1289,1313]" captionTargetBox="[237,1354,203,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-243@10.[233,1354,197,1264]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8–13. Triarthron lecontei. 8. Right antenna, dorsal view. 9. Mandibles, dorsal view. 10. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 11. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 12. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 13. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 11, 13), 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 9, 12), 0.75 mm (Fig. 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310890/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) rounded apically; anterior apophysis broadly triangular.
</paragraph>
